  "abstract": {
    "value": "Chiral allenes are readily accessed in a single-pot operation in the reaction of terminal alkynes, aldehydes, chiral secondary amines, and zinc halides in good yields (up to 77% yield) and excellent enantioselectivities (up to 99% ee) in toluene at 120 °C. The reaction proceeds through initial formation of chiral propargylamine intermediates with creation of a new stereogenic center and subsequent chirality transfer via an intramolecular hydride shift to produce chiral allenes with high enantiomeric purities.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
    "confidence": 0.98,
    "human_checked": false
  },
